Package mmj.pa

Class DistinctVariablesStmt

java.lang.Object
mmj.pa.ProofWorkStmt
mmj.pa.DistinctVariablesStmt
public class DistinctVariablesStmt extends ProofWorkStmt
DistinctVariablesStmt represents a single Metamath $d statement in a ProofWorksheet.

A proof may contain 0 -> n DistinctVariablesStmt's. They are used during Unification as *additions* to whatever $d statements are contained in the database for the theorem being proved.

  • Method Details

    • eliminateDvGroupsAlreadyPresent

      public static List<List<Var>> eliminateDvGroupsAlreadyPresent(DistinctVariablesStmt[] dvStmtArray, List<List<Var>> dvGroupsIn)
      Returns a dvGroup ArrayList of elements of the input dvGroup1 ArrayList which are not already specified by the contents of the input array of DistinctVariableStmt.

      For example, if the input dvGroup has an element <x,y,z> and the input dvStmtArray has an element <z,y,z,t> then the dvGroup element is not written to the output dvGroups ArrayList.

      Parameters:
      dvStmtArray - array of DistinctVariablesStmt
      dvGroupsIn - List of List of Var
      Returns:
      non-redundant dvGroups List.

    • load

      public String load(String firstToken) throws IOException, MMIOException, ProofAsstException
      Load Distinct Variable Statement.

      Distinct Variable group of variables must satisfy these edits:

      • two or more variables
      • each variable seq nbr < maxSeq
      • no duplicate variables

      Output/Updates

      • accum tokens and whitespace into stmtText
      • load Distinct Variable Group: "var[] dv" in the DistinctVariableStmt
      • return nextToken after trailing whitespace, the start of the next statement.
      Overrides:
      load in class ProofWorkStmt
      Parameters:
      firstToken - first token of the statement
      Returns:
      first token of the next statement.
      Throws:
      IOException - if IO error
      MMIOException - if an error occurred
